---
Locale-negotiation-slice-2 follow-up (#886): proves the gap named in
`design/pending/locale-negotiation-slice-2.md` is closed ‚Äî `app.web`
combines a real `Locale.current()` call with a message-bundle's own
`render` (via `app.bundle`'s `greet` wrapper) in one context, with no
`uses bynk.locale` anywhere in `app.web` itself.
---
suite app.web as unit {
  stub Locale.current() returns "en"

  case "renders the bundle's greeting through the wrapper" {
    let g <- greeting.call()
    expect g == "Hello"
  }
}
